                                     },
                       "message":  "NEWPROJECT-SAVE-WIRING: Ctrl+Shift+S Save-As to a new .rge-project tree\n\nWiring half of the Save-As feature (mirrors #274 PROJECT-SAVE-WIRING) over the\n#283 substrate save_world_as_new_project. editor-shell + rge-editor binary +\ntests; 0 Cargo.toml. editor-shell stays loader-free / rfd-free (Box\u003cdyn ...\u003e\nonly).\n\neditor-shell:\n- save_request.rs: new binary-owned seams NewProjectSaveDialog\n  (pick_new_project_dir) + NewProjectSaveHook (save_world_as_new_project -\u003e\n  created .rge-project path); new handle_save_as_new_project_request +\n  create_new_project_world helper. PIE-gated; cancel / no-dialog / no-hook /\n  hook-error all warn/info + no-op (mirrors handle_save_request). On success\n  adopts SaveSource::Project { path: \u003ccreated\u003e, name: \u003cfolder-derived\u003e } and\n  marks saved. A non-UTF-8 dir yields name: None and the save still succeeds\n  (the path is the source of truth; display_name falls back to it).\n- commands.rs: EditorKeyCommand::SaveAsProject; from_key_press gains a\n  ctrl\u0026\u0026shift branch (Ctrl+Shift+S -\u003e SaveAsProject) checked before the no-Shift\n  set; handle_key_command arm. window_event already passes ctrl+shift.\n- mod.rs: new_project_dialog / new_project_hook fields + None defaults in all 3\n  constructors + with_new_project_save_dialog / with_new_project_save_hook\n  builders + re-export. lib.rs: crate re-export.\n\nrge-editor binary: NewProjectSaveFileDialog (rfd pick_folder) +\nNewProjectSaveWriterHook (over rge_scene_loader::save_world_as_new_project),\nattached in all 3 launch modes.\n\nTests (editor-shell tests.rs, additive): success (adopt Project + folder name +\ndisplay_name + mark saved); cancel; missing dialog; missing hook; hook error;\nCtrl+Shift+S decode (and Ctrl+S unchanged); adopt-then-Ctrl+S routes through the\nexisting ProjectSaveHook. Existing Ctrl+S (Scene/Project silent) and\nNone -\u003e .rge-scene Save-As regressions stay green, unchanged.\n\nCloses the Save-As feature (substrate #283 + this wiring).\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
