                       "message":  "NEWPROJECT-SAVE-WIRING: docs-only correction — distinguish Ctrl+S .rge-scene Save-As from Ctrl+Shift+S new-project Save-As\n\nCodex post-exec review (NEEDS_CORRECTION): two stale doc blocks framed Save-As\nas scene-only / always SaveSource::Scene, now false since this PR ships\nCtrl+Shift+S new-.rge-project Save-As.\n\n- save_request.rs module doc: the Ctrl+S no-source Save-As produces a .rge-scene\n  SaveSource::Scene; Save-As to a NEW .rge-project tree is the separate\n  Ctrl+Shift+S handle_save_as_new_project_request gesture (adopts\n  SaveSource::Project).\n- mod.rs save_source field doc: a successful Save-As is no longer \"always\n  SaveSource::Scene\" — Ctrl+S (no source) -\u003e Scene, Ctrl+Shift+S -\u003e Project.\n\nStale-prose sweep also fixed the same false claim in\nrge-scene-loader/src/lib.rs (save_project_world_to_path doc): \"creating a NEW\nproject tree (Save-As) is a follow-up\" -\u003e cross-references\nsave_world_as_new_project (shipped #283).\n\nDocs-only, 0 Cargo.toml. Gate: VERIFY OK (7/7), 10/10 arch lints.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
